Also Known As
n/a

Summary
Happens when an organization places all faith in one thing, can be a service, product or a person.

Context
The organization believes that the ultimate weapon is going to solve the problems of the organization.

Symptoms and Consequences
-	Excess of enthusiasm in the team.
-	Organization has the view that a new solution that it was found is better than the old one.
-	Big desolation if it doesn’t solve the problems that are expected to solve.
-	Decisions are taken emotionally.
-	Big costs in terms of money and time.
-	Every or almost every critical task relies on the ultimate weapon.
-	If it is a person, he/she is not letting others get the same opportunities.

Causes
-	Lack of skepticism towards the new solution.
-	Emotions take over the people.
-	Bad management.
-	“Hero” culture. If it is a person, the person will solve.

Solution
-	Try to make a better diagnosis. Avoid complexity if it’s not necessary.
-	Evaluate trade-offs.
-	Try to innovate with the tool that is already in the organization.
-	Empower other people so they can highlight themselves.
-	Minimize dependencies.

Related Anti-patterns
Silver Bullet

